          "TITLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "-Fission mode fluctuations in the resonances of",
                " 235-U(N,F)."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "FACILITY": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "facility": [
                  "LINAC"
                ],
                "institute": "2ZZZGEL"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The Geel linac gelina was used as",
                " pulsed white neutron source. For the measurements",
                " in the 0.4 eV to 500 KeV range the machine parameters",
                " were 800 hz pulse repetition rate, 0.7 ns pulse width",
                " and 10 kw beam power at 100 MeV electrons. For the",
                " energy range from 0.006 eV to 25 eV the corresponding",
                " parameters were 40 hz, 2 micro-S and 1.5 to 2 kw,",
                " respectively."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "PHOTO"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Neutrons were produced in the beam stop target",
                " and moderated above and below the target. The direct",
                " target yield was shielded by 20 cm lead and 20 cm",
                " copper. A 0.1 g/cm2 10-B filter was used in the 800 hz",
                " measurements to reduce the flux of slow neutrons. The",
                " beam was tailored in a collimator to give a beam spot",
                " of 7 cm diameter at the fission chamber position.",
                ".Measurements with a 5 cm thick paraffin block in front",
                " of the fission chamber gave a thermal neutron flux,",
                " which was used as reference."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                ".The fission sample was prepared by vacuum evaporation",
                " of uf4. The fission layer had a diameter of 7 cm and a",
                " thickness of 47 micro-g/cm2. The isotopic composition",
                " was 99.8098%, 0.0638%, 0.0389%, and 0.0875% for",
                " 235-U, 234-U, 236-U and 238-U, respectively.",
                " The UF4-layer was supported by a 30 micro-g/cm2",
                " polyimide foil, spanned on an aluminium ring",
                " of 10 cm outer and 8 cm inner diameter. The polyimide",
                " foil was evaporated from both sides with gold",
                " layers of 40 micro-g/cm2 for electrical conductivity."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TOF"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "   A flight path of 8.83 m from from the target to",
                " the fission chamber was used."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "FISCH"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A twin frisch-gridded ionization chamber, in-",
                " cluding an ionization chamber for gamma-flash compen-",
                " sation, was used for the fission fragment detection.",
                " The two alpha-particle lines at 4.396 MeV and 4.773",
                " MeV from 235-U and 234-U, respectively, were used for",
                " absolute calibration."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "PART-DET": [
